# Next.js App Router Patterns

When creating pages:
- Server components by default (no "use client")
- Add "use client" only for interactivity (useState, useEffect, onClick, onChange)
- Use loading.tsx for suspense boundaries
- Use error.tsx for error boundaries

When creating API routes (route.ts):
- Export named functions: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
- Always validate auth first: const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
- Return NextResponse.json({ data }) for success
- Return NextResponse.json({ error: message }, { status: code }) for errors
- Parse body with request.json() for POST/PUT

When creating layouts:
- Dashboard layout checks auth and redirects to /login if not authenticated
- Root layout wraps in ThemeProvider and includes Toaster from sonner
- Use next/navigation for routing (useRouter, usePathname, redirect)
- Set metadata using generateMetadata() for SEO on public pages
